content.htmlText:
BEST HOLLYWOOD LOCATION with a Walk Score of 95!


Tons of restaurants within 3 blocks of house, and just a 10-minute walk to the Hollywood Walk of Fame, the Hollywood & Highland entertainment complex, The Dolby Theater (home of the Academy Awards and America's Got Talent), the original Chinese Theatre, and the El Capitan and Arclight theaters. There is also an LA Metro station for easy access to Universal Studios, LAX, downtown, etc.


Walk to all the Hollywood sites, and it's only 1 mile to Melrose shopping, 2.5 miles to the Grove/Farmer's Market, and 2.5 miles to West Hollywood. The Burbank studios (Warner Brothers, Disney, etc.) are only 1 exit away. See my Guidebook for recommendations within walking distance.


Fitness-minded guests will appreciate high-end treadmill, Tonal, and Far-Infrared sauna, as well as the easy walk to nearby Gold's gym, LA Fitness and Runyon Canyon for hiking.


Popular search terms for this tourist area: Hollywood, Griffith Park Observatory, Walk of Fame, Chinese Theater, Musician's Institute, American Academy of Dramatic Arts (AADA), Upright Citizen's Brigade (UCB), the Grove, Beverly Hills, Rodeo Drive, West Hollywood (WeHo), gay-friendly, GLBT, Westwood, UCLA, Larchmont, celebrity, TMZ, Hollywood Roosevelt, W Hotel, Universal Studios, Madam Tussaud's, Wanderlust, yoga, Hollywood & Highland, Jimmy Kimmel, Ellen Degeneres, Pantages, Santa Monica.

htmlDescription.htmlText:
Clean, bright bedroom in my shared home on ground floor with your own private/gated parking space. Comfy queen bed, washer/dryer in unit, weekly maid service, bottled water, central AC, super-fast WiFi, free Keurig and Nespresso coffee & walk to all of Hollywood. Home also includes a high-end treadmill and infrared sauna.

2022 Tesla Model Y available to rent for $125/day - message me if interested.

The space
** NOTE: Proof of Covid vaccination is required prior to check-in, as this is a shared home. You can also rest easy knowing I keep the place extremely clean, and disinfect all touch points and surfaces throughout the day. I also have a virus protection filter on my central AC/heater, and a powerful $800 Molekule air purifier, to ensure a clean and healthy environment at all times

There is an automatic discount based on number of days booked -- additional discounts are not available.

If you have a question that's not answered below, feel free to message me.

This is a private bedroom with a shared bathroom in a ground floor duplex. You may be sharing the entire home with just me, or you may have the home to yourself, depending on my travel schedule (I won't know in advance). Either way, I'll always be available via phone/text/email during your stay, to help you with anything you may need. There are no time restrictions - you may come and go as you please.

BEDROOM INCLUDES:
- Queen-size bed with Tuft & Needle mattress
- LCD TV with Apple TV+/HBO/Showtime/Netflix/Hulu/Amazon Prime
- Echo Show in room for music/news/general Info
- Workspace w/chair
- Wardrobe w/drawers
- Wall-mounted hair dryer
- 1 safe, private, gated parking space.
- Garden facing view

I PROVIDE:
- Fresh towels and linens
- Aveda soap/shampoo/conditioner
- Filtered and bottled water
- Some snacks and breakfast items (yogurt, coffee/tea).

OTHER PERKS INCLUDE:
- Keurig and Nespresso coffee makers with free coffee and tea
- Central air and heat
- Super-fast (200Mbps+) WiFi
- Pro NordicTrack Treadmill w/32" screen
- Tonal gym
- 2-person Far-Infrared Sauna
- Iron and washer/dryer in the unit
- Eco-friendly cleaning products

WHAT GUESTS LOVE MOST
- Central location
- free parking
- washer/dryer
- fast WiFi
- treadmill and sauna

WHAT TO CONSIDER
- Bathroom is shared (although it's clean, spacious, and well-equipped)
- To minimize noise, I ask that you not use kitchen or living room between midnight-8am.

If you're tired of traveling, take a night off -- order delivery from one of the hundreds of nearby restaurants and relax with an LCD TV and free Netflix/HBO/Showtime/Hulu.

Sip your morning coffee on the garden picnic area, surrounded by butterflies, birds and squirrels as you plan your day.

Home is safe and high-tech with voice-controlled lighting and music, and a digital front door lock (no key to lose!).

Guest access
Shared use of house, including full bathroom, living room, kitchen and backyard.

During your stay
The house works on a digital code entry so arrangements can be made for you to gain entry any time before midnight.

I am usually available for questions and help getting around LA, either in person or via phone or text.

Other things to note
This room is for non-smokers ONLY - if you book the room you are agreeing that you are NOT a smoker and will therefore not be smoking ANYWHERE during your stay.

License number
HSR22-003759

features.title: Booking Protection Guarantee

features.title: Check-In Guarantee
features.subtitle: If you can’t check into your home and the Host cannot resolve the issue, we’ll find you a similar or better home for the length of your original stay, or we’ll refund you.

features.title: Get-What-You-Booked Guarantee
features.subtitle: If at any time during your stay you find your listing isn't as advertised—for example, the refrigerator stops working and your Host can’t easily fix it, or it has fewer bedrooms than listed—you'll have three days to report it and we’ll find you a similar or better home, or we’ll refund you.
